From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 05:15:29 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 22/25] Intra-commit ordering pinned (test 26) + classification
 tests + flag-3 pin: all v1 capability bits set
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Capability bit 1<<5 flips: the per-root commit report now carries its
pinned §4.2 ordering guarantee — within one commit, the committed-side
entry (end(commit)) precedes the table update (onRootCommitted) precedes
every fold the commit causes (onBatchRetired, plural) precedes the
host-mutation window precedes layout effects. A consumer snapshotting its
mirror at end(commit) captures the PRE-commit {retired set, generation}:
the commit's own motion cannot mask foreign motion (the binding's
mount-fixup baseline, spec §5.10). Pinned with a two-token retiring
commit + mutation + layout probe in the Commit file.

Classification tests 1/3/4/5/6 (test 2 was S1's): discrete-event writes
urgent and distinct from the ambient default batch; timer/network writes
ambient default; flushSync writes urgent, committing synchronously;
nested scopes classify per callstack both ways; per-write context is
stable across interleaved scopes in one event (the fork side of the
library batch() contract).

Appendix B flag 3 pinned: a re-wrapped async-action continuation claims
the entangled action lane and gets the SAME parked token (explicit merge
rule); a bare continuation classifies as ambient default; the parked
token still retires exactly once, uncommitted, when the action settles.

EXTERNAL_RUNTIME_CAPABILITIES is now bits 0-8 == every planned v1 bit,
on both sides of the handshake. 47 fork tests green on all four
channels; 15 upstream suites green; linc, prettier, flow dom-node clean.
